
=============================
    FULL GIT COMMAND GUIDE
=============================

This file includes commands for:
- Pushing code/files to main
- Pushing files to branches (dev1/dev2)
- Cloning, committing, pulling, and merging
- One-liners for quick use

=============================
📦 CLONE REPOSITORY (First Time)
=============================
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo.git
cd your-repo

=============================
🌿 WORKING ON MAIN BRANCH
=============================

✅ Switch to main branch:
git checkout main

✅ Add a new file (e.g., notes.txt):
git add notes.txt

✅ Commit changes:
git commit -m "Added notes.txt"

✅ Push to main branch:
git push origin main

✅ 🔁 One-liner:
git checkout main && git add notes.txt && git commit -m "Added notes.txt" && git push origin main

✅ Push all files in project to main:
git add .
git commit -m "Updated full project"
git push origin main

=============================
🌿 WORKING ON BRANCHES (dev1 / dev2)
=============================

✅ Create and switch to a branch:
git checkout -b dev1        # or dev2

✅ Switch to existing branch:
git checkout dev1           # or dev2

✅ Add specific file (e.g., demo.txt):
git add demo.txt

✅ Or add all files:
git add .

✅ Commit your changes:
git commit -m "Updated demo.txt"

✅ Push to your branch:
git push origin dev1        # or dev2

✅ Pull latest updates from branch:
git pull origin dev1        # or dev2

✅ 🔁 One-liner:
git add . && git commit -m "Updated files" && git push origin dev1   # or dev2

=============================
🔁 MERGING TO MAIN (After Review)
=============================

✅ On GitHub:
- Create Pull Request from dev1 or dev2 to main
- Review and Merge

✅ Then update local main:
git checkout main
git pull origin main

=============================
🧼 OPTIONAL CLEANUP
=============================

✅ Delete a merged branch (locally):
git branch -d dev1

✅ Delete a branch from remote:
git push origin --delete dev1

=============================

End of Git Command Guide
